com.unboundid.ldap.sdk.unboundidds.extensions

Class GetBackupCompatibilityDescriptorExtendedResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.unboundid.ldap.sdk.LDAPResult
      • com.unboundid.ldap.sdk.ExtendedResult
        • com.unboundid.ldap.sdk.unboundidds.extensions.GetBackupCompatibilityDescriptorExtendedResult
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    LDAPResponse, java.io.Serializable

    @ThreadSafety(level=COMPLETELY_THREADSAFE)
public final class GetBackupCompatibilityDescriptorExtendedResult
extends ExtendedResult
    This class provides an implementation of an extended result that can be used to retrieve backup compatibility data for a Directory Server backend.
    NOTE: This class, and other classes within the com.unboundid.ldap.sdk.unboundidds package structure, are only supported for use against Ping Identity, UnboundID, and Alcatel-Lucent 8661 server products. These classes provide support for proprietary functionality or for external specifications that are not considered stable or mature enough to be guaranteed to work in an interoperable way with other types of LDAP servers.

    The OID for this extended result is 1.3.6.1.4.1.30221.2.6.31. If the request was processed successfully, then the response will have a value with the following encoding: 
       GetBackupCompatibilityDescriptorResult ::= SEQUENCE {
        descriptor     [0] OCTET STRING,
        properties     [1] SEQUENCE OF OCTET STRING OPTIONAL,
        ... }
    See Also:
    GetBackupCompatibilityDescriptorExtendedRequest, IdentifyBackupCompatibilityProblemsExtendedRequest, Serialized Form
